subSubSection.paragraph:
Cephalothorax.
Frontal apotome (
Fig. 4E
) slightly rounded, 137–157 μm long; 191–196 μm wide. Frontal setae 34–49 μm long. Distance between Dc1 and Dc2 5–7 μm; between Dc2 and Dc3 232–239 μm; between Dc3 and Dc4 5–7 μm (
Fig. 4F
). Thoracic horn with multiple branches.

Head.
Head capsule slightly rounded. Antenna as in 
Figure 4C
. Length of antennal segments (in μm): 47, 20, 10, 10, 5. Blade 37 μm long. AR 1.17. Lauterborn organs 2 μm long. Pecten epipharyngis (
Fig. 4B
) consisting of 3 platelets, median with 3 teeth; lateral each with 4 teeth. Mandible (
Fig. 4D
) 129 μm long with apical tooth and 3 inner teeth. Seta subdentalis 5 μm long; seta interna with about 25 branches. Mola with weak spines. Mentum (
Fig. 4A
) 110 μm wide, with 8 pairs of mental teeth. Ventromental plate 127 μm wide, with anteriorly produced median ends and without posterior projection, distance between plates 17 μm.
